The paper deals with motion planning problems for autonomous robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The methods presented in the paper are also relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) as proximity queries are important for object detection and tracking. The paper involves bounding curves in a convex region, which is a common problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also deals with collision detection, which is a key topic in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents efficient methods for computing bounds on obstacle proximity, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves decision-making and planning.
